text: Matea Sumajstorčić (born 5 April 1999) is a Croatian swimmer. In 2019, she represented Croatia at the 2019 World Aquatics Championships held in Gwangju, South Korea. She competed in the women's 800 metre freestyle and women's 1500 metre freestyle events. In both events she did not advance to compete in the final. ==References== Category:1999 births Category:Living people Category:Croatian female swimmers Category:Place of birth missing (living people) Category:Croatian female freestyle swimmers
